According to people familiar with the matter  the bank may let go of a minimum of four floors  as it looks to cut costs and transition to a permanent hybrid working model during the COVID-19 pandemic.In Hong Kong  Standard Chartered was giving up a number of floors across main offices  the media outlet reported in February. In an e-mailed statement  the lender said about 80% of its Singapore employees are on a flexible working arrangement but refused to comment on its office rental plans.
